genSynthFlow

Class SynthPop

  • java.lang.Object
    • genSynthFlow.SynthPop

  • public class SynthPop
extends java.lang.Object
    Creates a synthetic population of workers travelling from OAs to WZs. Iterates OA origins to minimize counts errors with census-derived flows.
    Version:
    1.1, August 2014
    Author:
    Richard Thomas

    • Field Detail

      • RESHUFFLE_OA_CAND_SEQUENCE_FOR_EVERY_WORKER

        private static final boolean RESHUFFLE_OA_CAND_SEQUENCE_FOR_EVERY_WORKER
        Shuffled candidate OA sequence for every worker? (Otherwise done only once for all workers in each WZ) Note: uses MUCH more memory due to having a candidate OA list for all workers instead of just one per WZ (For just Bristol UA, WZs = 484, population = 61281 for 2-5km - executable size = 55MB vs 289MB)
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • ITERATE_USING_PROPORTIONAL_MISMATCH

        private static final boolean ITERATE_USING_PROPORTIONAL_MISMATCH
        Use the proportion of each OA count mismatch to the total count from the census-derived OA count total when deciding whether to switch a worker from being re-assigned from one OA to another. If false, then iteration decision will be simply made on whether it reduces the sum of magnitudes of the differences between current and target OA counts (a method which is generally much slower to converge and can result in proportional large errors in OA counts).
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • ITERATION_TABLE_LOG_FILENAME

        private static final java.lang.String ITERATION_TABLE_LOG_FILENAME
        Filename to write diagnostic table of all OA differences from target values at each active iteration (one where OA origins switches occur). (Set to null if diagnostics not required)
        See Also:
